The long-tailed mockingbird (Mimus longicaudatus) is a species of bird in the family Mimidae. It is found in dry scrubland and woodland in western Ecuador and Peru (north of Caman√°).
The bird favours open habitats with scattered low bushes and shrubs, such as forest edge and young second growth, montane scrub.It is frequently found in gardens and parks. It often feeds on the ground, running forwards on relatively long legs.